I'll solve this step by step by calculating each of the required financial metrics.

1. **Free Cash Flow (FCF)**
   FCF = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities - Capital Expenditures
   FCF = -1,919,526.63 - 3,415,664.34 = -5,335,190.97

2. **Return on Assets (ROA)**
   ROA = (Net Income / Total Assets) × 100
   ROA = (99,532.29 / 21,737,442.99) × 100 = 0.46%

3. **Return on Equity (ROE)**
   ROE = (Net Income / Total Owner's Equity) × 100
   ROE = (99,532.29 / 16,099,532.29) × 100 = 0.62%

4. **Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio**
   Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Net Income
   Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio = -1,919,526.63 / 99,532.29 = -19.29

5. **Net Profit Margin**
   Net Profit Margin = (Net Income / Total Revenue) × 100
   Net Profit Margin = (99,532.29 / 836,813.79) × 100 = 11.89%

6. **Gross Profit Margin**
   Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100
   Gross Profit Margin = (291,843.79 / 836,813.79) × 100 = 34.88%
